# General Project Conventions

## Language

- All code, comments, commit messages, and PR descriptions must be written in English.

## Project Overview

- This is a Go project implementing an MCP (Model Context Protocol) server for Cloudflare.
- Module path: `github.com/M-Yamashita01/cloudflare-mcp-go`

## Git Conventions

- Use conventional commit prefixes: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `ci:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `test:`
- Keep commit messages concise and descriptive.

## Code Quality

- Run `golangci-lint` before committing. The project uses: errcheck, govet, staticcheck, unused, ineffassign, gosimple, gofmt, goimports, misspell.
- Use `goimports` with local prefix `github.com/M-Yamashita01/cloudflare-mcp-go`.
